narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Lots of review of grammar and new vocabulary. This is the first course in which I noticed my Italian speaking skills to improve to a relatively conversational level.

Fundamental speaking, writing, and reading skills. Deborah was very encouraging and such a helpful professor throughout the entire semester. I especially think I improved my speaking skills in her class.

Developed skills in Italian grammar, vocabulary, and structure. This class really helped improve my Italian from the previous two semesters, especially in regards to confidence in the language and oral presentation.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course is very consistent, fair, and structured. The professors are all good and the assignments are rarely stressful. The asynchronous day on Friday is also a wonderful perk!

Strengths: Deborah is an amazing and caring professor and wants you to succeed in her course and have fun with Italian. There are six exams throughout the semester, which is a lot but forces you to study the material along the way. Lots of opportunities to speak in Italian during class with other classmates. Weaknesses: I wish there was more focus on Italian culture, however this class focused more on it than the previous two semesters.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. The Italian department is wonderful and the language is beautiful.
Yes, I learned a lot in this course and am so glad I improved my speaking skills greatly.
I would certainly recommend this class to a student who is studying Italian and wants to improve on their skills.
